quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  3,121,"And [remember] when you left your home in the morning to position the believers for the battle [of ’Uhud]; and Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  3,122,"When two parties from among you were about to lose courage, but Allah was their protector. Let the believers put their trust in Allah"
  3,123,Allah had helped you at Badr when you were weak; then fear Allah so that you may be grateful
  3,124,"[Remember] when you said to the believers, “Will it not suffice you that your Lord will help you by sending down three thousand angels?”"
  3,125,"Yes, if you stay patient and fear Allah, and the enemy should launch a surprise attack on you, your Lord will help you with five thousand marked angels"
  3,126,"Allah ordained this only as glad tidings for you, and to reassure your hearts thereby. Victory only comes from Allah, the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"
  3,127,"in order to destroy a section of the disbelievers or disgrace them, so they may turn back utterly disappointed"
  3,128,"It is not for you [O Prophet] to decide whether He will accept their repentance or punish them, for they are wrongdoers"
  3,129,"To Allah belongs all that is in the heavens and all that is on earth. He forgives whom He wills and punishes whom He wills, and Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"